e bar, casually poured himself a glass of brandy from a flat bottle, swallowed, wiped his mouth with his wrist, gave his cap a slap, and headed for the door. Krause lowered his knife and fork crosswise onto his plate and loudly said, “Wait! That’ll be twenty pfennigs!”

The electrician, with his hand already on the doorknob, looked back. “I thought I was at home here.”

“You don’t intend to pay?” asked Krause.

